<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 99-12-01 - Release of a Low Inertia Flexplate Assembly</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi991201" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>99-12-01</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>January, 1999</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engines</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Release of a Low Inertia Flexplate Assembly</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>International&#174; T 444E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>Low Inertia Flexplate Assembly</title>
                <para>A new steel flexplate and ring gear assembly has been released for production and service. The
                    change applies to all T 444E engines (serial number 891811 and higher) using Allison AT &#38; MT
                    model automatic transmissions.
                </para>
                <para>For the 1999 Model Year (serial number 891811 and higher) the grey iron flywheel, steel flexplate,
                    and grey iron flexplate adapter for both Allison AT &#38; MT automatic transmissions will be removed
                    and replaced with a steel flexplate and ring gear assembly. This assembly will be mounted to a grey
                    iron flexplate adapter/counterweight.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
            <title></title>
            <para>
                <title>1999 Model Year Engines</title>
            </para>
            <para>The following tables list the transmission components and their quantities for each of the
                transmission models.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When servicing 1999 M.Y. flexplate components, use caution to install only the correct parts
                        (see the appropriate table below) for engine serial number 891811 and higher.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>For 1999 M.Y. T 444E engines (serial number 891811 or higher) equipped with
